1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,000
previously on Dumbgeons and Dragons.

2
00:00:02,879 --> 00:00:10,080
In the room you're in now, there is a statue in the center of the room of a god named Loth.

3
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:17,359
And in the portal, you see the face of an ebony-skinned, white-haired drow.

4
00:00:17,359 --> 00:00:22,879
And he says, you adventurers have had quite the journey, haven't you?

5
00:00:22,879 --> 00:00:27,679
You are the three who I need in order to get the power.

6
00:00:28,640 --> 00:00:30,160
Oh, this fucking guy.

7
00:00:33,759 --> 00:00:35,519
That was a game, right?

8
00:00:35,519 --> 00:00:39,119
And what makes you think we're going to tell you?

9
00:00:39,119 --> 00:00:42,640
Well, you're never going to get out of the dungeon without telling me.

10
00:00:43,519 --> 00:00:44,560
I've heard that one before.

11
00:00:45,120 --> 00:00:48,560
I need to know where to get the train.

12
00:00:48,560 --> 00:00:52,640
You continue walking down this hallway and it takes you through a winding path.

13
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:55,520
You see a false stone wall.

14
00:00:55,520 --> 00:01:02,880
It pulls out and towards the corner and it reveals an unlocked wooden door.

15
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:03,760
Good catch.

16
00:01:03,760 --> 00:01:06,480
Too good to be true or too good to pass up.

17
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:08,000
What do you guys think?

18
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:09,200
Too good to pass up.

19
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:17,120
There is a mosaic of legendary monsters and a buzzing noise can be heard.

20
00:01:17,680 --> 00:01:26,400
Flint, you are swiped at by a dragon-esque looking statue.

21
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:26,960
Bring it.

22
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:35,360
And as it punches through the wall, the wall crumbles and out pour four 10-foot wide,

23
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:37,520
hairy, huge spiders.

24
00:01:37,520 --> 00:01:41,680
Four giant wasps about the size of halflings zip quickly past your head.

25
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:43,120
It's getting a bit crowded in here.

26
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:47,840
With your leaping jump, crumbles the final gargoyle in the room.

27
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:54,640
When you hear another buzz and you see a blue orb and out steps Tibby.

28
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:58,080
You guys ready to blow this pop stand or what?

29
00:01:58,080 --> 00:02:02,880
And then as quick as it began, it ends.

30
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:07,520
You look around and you quickly realize that you are no longer in Faerun.

31
00:02:07,519 --> 00:02:16,159
We open on a field to the east of Mirabar.

32
00:02:16,159 --> 00:02:18,240
It's on a high hill to the west.

33
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:23,840
You see the town of Mirabar and to the east, the wide open plains of Faerun.

34
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:29,680
The static in the air quickly forms animals scatter from the area

35
00:02:29,680 --> 00:02:37,039
and this blue orb appears and you are back in Faerun outside of Mirabar.

36
00:02:37,039 --> 00:02:38,319
Not in the dungeon.

37
00:02:38,319 --> 00:02:44,000
And you look to Mirabar and you see plumes of smoke coming up from the city.

38
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:48,319
You are a bit stunned having just stepped through the portal

39
00:02:48,319 --> 00:02:52,319
and experiencing what you have just seen and done.

40
00:02:52,319 --> 00:02:58,319
Thea now owns a book of the druids, which brings into question some thoughts she had

41
00:02:58,319 --> 00:03:01,919
on what it means to be a druid and in control of her powers.

42
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:09,680
Flint, as you step through the portal, you hear the anguished cries of Bort,

43
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:18,320
a dragonborn hunter-ranger, screaming at you for having torn him from his land and world.

44
00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:20,480
I did not ask for this.

45
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,480
Just a heads up.

46
00:03:22,480 --> 00:03:23,680
But you have it now.

47
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:25,360
But I mean, if you're going to blame someone,

48
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:27,520
don't blame the guy that just had it thrust upon him.

49
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:31,840
Let's just take a minute and you can maybe discuss amongst yourselves

50
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:35,439
in character some of the things you've seen and done

51
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:40,560
and how you're feeling about now knowing that there are parallel worlds,

52
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:45,280
not just planes as you were used to with the guild,

53
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:47,439
but parallel worlds in other universes.

54
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:54,640
Thea sits down on the ground and pulls out a joint and just lights up and is like,

55
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:55,600
Oh, Jesus.

56
00:03:57,600 --> 00:04:00,480
Yeah, guys, this is a lot to take in.

57
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:03,440
I mean, those guys seem great and all.

58
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:07,360
But what the hell is going on?

59
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:15,600
I thought we were dealing with dragons and that was crazy enough for someone

60
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:17,600
who's just a simple person.

61
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:21,439
And now I find out, oh, there's whole other dimensions.

62
00:04:21,439 --> 00:04:22,800
There's whole other worlds.

63
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:27,600
There's whole other groups of people that we don't even know about.

64
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:29,680
And now one of them is stuck in Flint.

65
00:04:30,319 --> 00:04:30,879
Yep.

66
00:04:30,879 --> 00:04:33,280
And the animals, man, the animals.

67
00:04:34,160 --> 00:04:35,120
Remember that elephant?

68
00:04:36,319 --> 00:04:38,319
Yeah, I don't know.

69
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:44,080
If I was a religious person, I would be having a crisis of faith.

70
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:51,280
Since I'm not, I kind of just want to go like hide in the woods.

71
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:54,400
That's kind of my go-to to feel better.

72
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:58,560
But we got a lot of shit we have to do.

73
00:04:58,560 --> 00:05:00,240
We have people counting on us.

74
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:02,320
What's going on over there in Miravar?

75
00:05:02,320 --> 00:05:03,520
The whole town's on fire.

76
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:07,120
What happened since we left the dungeon?

77
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:08,960
How long have we even been gone?

78
00:05:08,960 --> 00:05:10,640
Oh, God, that's a good question.

79
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:12,640
I wonder if time works the same.

80
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:13,600
Exactly.

81
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:17,120
I look at Flint's face and I throw him a joint.

82
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:23,280
And I say, buddy, you look worse than you did after you got out of the Fist of the Iron Dawn.

83
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:27,680
This is much needed, for sure.

84
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:29,439
Flint, do you want to make a constitution check?

85
00:05:30,639 --> 00:05:31,199
Yeah, right.

86
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:33,439
That is a 16.

87
00:05:33,439 --> 00:05:34,800
Bort rolled a 20.

88
00:05:36,959 --> 00:05:41,680
Out of Flint's mouth, which you guys have experienced this before,

89
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:45,280
Bort begins to scream.

90
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:46,800
It's like it kind of fades in.

91
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:49,840
Why did you bring me back here?

92
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:50,800
Why did you bring me here?

93
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:51,760
Where am I?

94
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:55,920
The elix shuffles back on the ground away from Flint.

95
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:57,440
He said I wanted to come back.

96
00:05:57,440 --> 00:06:00,240
I did not want to come here with you.

97
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:02,160
I look at you, Lara.

98
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:06,720
But if the choice was that or die, isn't this a better choice?

99
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:07,760
I don't know.

100
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:13,760
What if we can get you out of his body, into a new body somehow?

101
00:06:13,759 --> 00:06:16,560
Do you have that sort of power in this world?

102
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:17,439
Maybe.

103
00:06:17,439 --> 00:06:17,839
Maybe.

104
00:06:18,879 --> 00:06:20,319
We can certainly search.

105
00:06:22,079 --> 00:06:23,599
Flint, you want to make a con check?

106
00:06:23,599 --> 00:06:25,279
That is a 18.

107
00:06:25,279 --> 00:06:26,719
He rolled a six.

108
00:06:26,719 --> 00:06:28,719
Bort is gone and Flint is back.

109
00:06:28,719 --> 00:06:29,680
Flint, where did you go?

110
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:30,480
What did that feel like?

111
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:31,439
What's going on, buddy?

112
00:06:31,439 --> 00:06:32,399
Tell me.

113
00:06:32,399 --> 00:06:35,519
It does not feel good when that happens, I'll tell you that much.

114
00:06:36,079 --> 00:06:38,959
So is Flint aware and can hear everything that's happening?

115
00:06:38,959 --> 00:06:41,599
Or is it like he has a fugue state and blacks out

116
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:44,000
and finds himself in a completely different location?

117
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,400
Why am I covered in tattoos?

118
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:53,680
Basically, how I am going to treat it is there are two drivers at the wheel.

119
00:06:54,480 --> 00:07:01,920
When Bort wins the con, he takes control and he can say and do whatever he wants

120
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,680
Flint's body to say and do.

121
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:08,800
They probably not right now, but probably very soon I'm going to have Flint and Bort

122
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:13,439
have a conversation about what they want.

123
00:07:13,439 --> 00:07:17,040
But for the rest of the episode, we're going to say Flint is in control.

124
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:23,040
But Flint, you feel like there's someone always pulling at your mind

125
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:25,600
to try and get control of your body.

126
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:26,000
Sweet.

127
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,920
So I have to concentrate all the time?

128
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:28,980
Yeah.

129
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:31,280
That sounds uncomfortable.

130
00:07:31,280 --> 00:07:32,480
This is going to go great, guys.

131
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:35,600
Maybe you don't want to take that joint now.

132
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,480
Maybe you don't want that.

133
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:39,840
Fuck it, Bort.

134
00:07:39,840 --> 00:07:40,639
You just take over.

135
00:07:40,639 --> 00:07:42,000
You just take over.

136
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,120
Bort, I'm tired.

137
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,879
I need some Flint time.

138
00:07:44,879 --> 00:07:46,560
So you just go right ahead.

139
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:50,879
Should we go down to Mirabar or should we just go back to Luskin?

140
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:53,840
That's where we were going to take the box, right?

141
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:55,680
We need to go get your armor.

142
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:56,240
Oh, my God.

143
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:57,040
Yes.

144
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:58,000
Yeah, right.

145
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:59,680
I've forgotten all about my armor.

146
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:02,319
I just get a tingly feeling all up and down.

147
00:08:02,319 --> 00:08:04,800
And possibly a new trucker hat for Donnie.

148
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:09,280
Guys, we have to go back because Primsbane probably has control

149
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:11,600
of the entire Mirabar army by now.

150
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:16,720
We can't just let them run rampant over the whole world.

151
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:18,960
Thea lays down in the grass.

152
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:22,080
It's like, can't we?

153
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:29,120
Thea's having a crisis of druidness.

154
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:34,159
As you lay down in the grass, you begin to feel a rumble.

155
00:08:35,199 --> 00:08:36,000
In the ground.

156
00:08:37,359 --> 00:08:37,839
Pardon me.

157
00:08:40,959 --> 00:08:42,879
Not that kind of rumble.

158
00:08:42,879 --> 00:08:48,479
You begin to feel a very even-paced cadence.

159
00:08:49,039 --> 00:08:51,199
Guys, someone's marching.

160
00:08:51,199 --> 00:08:55,519
And as you look to the east over the top of another large hill,

161
00:08:55,519 --> 00:09:02,399
you see the remaining soldiers of the Axe of Mirabar marching towards Mirabar.

162
00:09:03,199 --> 00:09:03,600
Oh!

163
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:05,519
Guys, they haven't made it there yet.

164
00:09:05,519 --> 00:09:07,840
Primsbane probably isn't controlling them yet.

165
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:12,399
If we can cut them off, maybe we can work together to stop Primsbane,

166
00:09:12,399 --> 00:09:16,720
and then we can try and figure out what to do to get Bort out of Flint

167
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:21,919
because this is an unmanageable situation.

168
00:09:21,919 --> 00:09:23,759
Oh, it is not working for anybody.

169
00:09:24,319 --> 00:09:24,879
Okay.

170
00:09:24,879 --> 00:09:26,720
Thea, are you okay?

171
00:09:27,279 --> 00:09:28,159
Sure, let's go.

172
00:09:28,159 --> 00:09:28,799
Oh, yeah.

173
00:09:32,319 --> 00:09:33,679
So that joint kicked in.

174
00:09:33,679 --> 00:09:35,120
You're a bit more relaxed.

175
00:09:35,120 --> 00:09:36,719
So Thea does a somersault.

176
00:09:36,719 --> 00:09:39,600
Just like a little, like, woo, in the grass and gets up

177
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:41,439
and starts walking towards the army.

178
00:09:41,439 --> 00:09:43,759
Everybody else just does laissez-faire about it,

179
00:09:43,759 --> 00:09:46,399
or you guys have a different notice?

180
00:09:46,399 --> 00:09:47,199
I'm ready.

181
00:09:47,199 --> 00:09:48,639
I want to cut them off,

182
00:09:48,639 --> 00:09:55,600
and if we can get an army on our side fighting this dumb bastard,

183
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:56,879
I'm happy to do it.

184
00:09:57,439 --> 00:09:58,879
Let's get some help.

185
00:09:58,879 --> 00:10:00,080
How far out are they?

186
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:04,159
They're a fair ways out, maybe just under a kilometer,

187
00:10:04,159 --> 00:10:06,799
but you're about halfway between them and Mirabar.

188
00:10:06,799 --> 00:10:08,559
Do you guys want to hop on?

189
00:10:08,559 --> 00:10:11,279
I know you shouldn't smoke and fly, but...

190
00:10:12,799 --> 00:10:15,039
But Guacamole would be the one flying.

191
00:10:15,039 --> 00:10:15,840
Yeah.

192
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:17,679
Do you guys want to hop on and get there fast?

193
00:10:17,679 --> 00:10:18,320
Let's do it.

194
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:19,600
Good. I don't want to run.

195
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:20,080
And?

196
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:22,000
What if Guacamole gets a contact high?

197
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:25,360
My joint is done.

198
00:10:27,519 --> 00:10:29,039
I pulled that back pretty fast.

199
00:10:29,039 --> 00:10:34,559
This will also give us a chance to observe from a distance

200
00:10:34,559 --> 00:10:41,439
or easily retreatable if they're under Prim's Bane's control, hopefully.

201
00:10:41,439 --> 00:10:44,639
Guacamole has really good sight vision, and we can...

202
00:10:45,279 --> 00:10:46,320
Really good sight vision?

203
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:46,820
Yeah.

204
00:10:47,519 --> 00:10:48,399
Yeah, sight vision.

205
00:10:49,039 --> 00:10:50,000
Shut up, Russ.

206
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:52,000
I'm not high right now, actually.

207
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:55,679
Those words just came out of my mouth.

208
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:58,160
Guacamole has really good vision.

209
00:10:58,720 --> 00:10:59,840
You bastard.

210
00:10:59,840 --> 00:11:03,120
And we can talk to each other telepathically,

211
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:07,360
so I can ask Guacamole if they look like...

212
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:08,560
Because they looked weird, right?

213
00:11:08,560 --> 00:11:09,600
They looked undead.

214
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:10,080
Yes.

215
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:10,580
Right?

216
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:14,640
So, okay, I summon Guacamole.

217
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:16,080
Gwak!

218
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:24,960
And my wonderful Jade Serpentine Owl.

219
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:28,080
Comes forth from the...

220
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:30,800
Is that what you say when Guacamole comes up?

221
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:32,080
Yeah, I do now.

222
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:32,580
Perfect.

223
00:11:33,520 --> 00:11:34,480
Hi, Theodos.

224
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:36,180
Gwak!

225
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:39,840
So, yeah, we telepathically communicate.

226
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:42,720
So we hop on, because she's already wearing a saddle,

227
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:44,560
and we... and off we fly.

228
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:46,480
You fly up and you're up in the air.

229
00:11:46,480 --> 00:11:48,960
You're able to see Mirabar better.

230
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:52,560
And it looks like there are buildings on fire.

231
00:11:52,560 --> 00:11:57,600
You can see soldiers of the acts of Mirabar in the city,

232
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:59,840
and you can see people running from them.

233
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:01,520
So the soldiers in town are...

234
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:02,320
Oh, but we knew that.

235
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:04,400
The soldiers in town were all overtaken.

236
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:10,880
Yes, and as you fly more towards the army

237
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:13,360
that's coming towards the city,

238
00:12:13,360 --> 00:12:16,080
they see you and they stop their position,

239
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:19,120
and you hear them readying their archers

240
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:21,680
as you fly down and near them.

241
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:23,200
And they yell up to you.

242
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:25,120
If you don't want to be shot from the sky,

243
00:12:25,920 --> 00:12:28,160
you should probably come down now.

244
00:12:28,160 --> 00:12:31,600
Do they say that in unison, or does like a dude say that,

245
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:35,200
or do they say it like a bunch of people say it at different times?

246
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:38,000
A single dude at the front says that.

247
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,840
Can I see how they look from here?

248
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:43,680
From what you can see, they look to be normal.

249
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:48,720
They are all wearing full armor and with their headgear and stuff, but...

250
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:50,320
Can Guacamole see anything?

251
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:52,160
You or Guacamole see nothing

252
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:54,480
that appears out of the ordinary with them.

253
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:54,980
Okay.

254
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:58,879
Guacamole lands like a good, you know,

255
00:12:58,879 --> 00:13:03,600
a decent distance away, like away, you know, for safety.

256
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:06,800
And the guy who yelled at you,

257
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:09,520
he looks like he's got much finer plate mail.

258
00:13:09,520 --> 00:13:13,840
You could say he's probably the commander or leader of this squad.

259
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:15,920
Then he yells out to you and says,

260
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:18,880
you need to start explaining to yourselves what's going on here.

261
00:13:18,879 --> 00:13:20,559
Why is there fire in Mirabar?

262
00:13:20,559 --> 00:13:22,879
And what are you doing flying towards us?

263
00:13:23,759 --> 00:13:26,799
Guys, he seems like he doesn't know anything about what's going on.

264
00:13:26,799 --> 00:13:27,840
This is perfect.

265
00:13:30,639 --> 00:13:31,439
What's going on?

266
00:13:32,559 --> 00:13:33,519
What's your name, sir?

267
00:13:33,519 --> 00:13:35,600
I'm Commander Hammerstryker,

268
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:37,919
and I am the commander of the acts of Mirabar.

269
00:13:37,919 --> 00:13:39,279
Okay, Hammy, listen up.

270
00:13:39,279 --> 00:13:40,480
You want to make a history check first?

271
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:43,039
Are we all making history checks?

272
00:13:43,039 --> 00:13:43,840
Yeah, everybody can.

273
00:13:44,160 --> 00:13:45,440
History.

274
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:48,500
16.

275
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:49,620
19.

276
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:52,639
16, only because I rolled a 10.

277
00:13:52,639 --> 00:13:54,000
That could have been real good, though.

278
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,480
You all know that the acts of Mirabar

279
00:13:56,480 --> 00:14:00,800
is commanded by Commander Torgar Hammerstryker,

280
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:06,000
and he has been the commander of the militia and the army in Mirabar

281
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,240
for close to 300 years now.

282
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:10,639
So that, to you, checks out.

283
00:14:10,639 --> 00:14:16,639
Hammy, my man, Ham the man, Ham the man.

284
00:14:16,639 --> 00:14:17,360
Who are you?

285
00:14:20,319 --> 00:14:24,559
I'm Thea Amastasia, and these are my compadres.

286
00:14:25,120 --> 00:14:26,000
What's your group name?

287
00:14:30,639 --> 00:14:32,080
None of your fucking business.

288
00:14:32,639 --> 00:14:33,360
That's our group name.

289
00:14:33,360 --> 00:14:35,919
Oh, let's dial it down a notch there.

290
00:14:35,919 --> 00:14:39,519
You see some of the soldiers get a little more agitated.

291
00:14:39,519 --> 00:14:40,399
Sorry, I'm sorry.

292
00:14:41,199 --> 00:14:42,240
Someone else start talking.

293
00:14:43,679 --> 00:14:45,519
Elbow Flint, go talk to him.

294
00:14:45,519 --> 00:14:46,879
You've got your charm belt.

295
00:14:48,399 --> 00:14:50,480
Dwarves love to other dwarves.

296
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:51,600
It's all the dwarf love.

297
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:54,559
I put my axe away, and I walk up and I say,

298
00:14:55,279 --> 00:14:58,399
Torgar Hammerstryker, you've come just in time.

299
00:14:58,399 --> 00:15:02,240
There are some serious problems going on in Mirabar.

300
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:04,879
Well, I see that, but what is happening?

301
00:15:04,879 --> 00:15:05,919
Sorry, who are you?

302
00:15:05,919 --> 00:15:06,879
My apologies.

303
00:15:06,879 --> 00:15:08,399
I'm Flint Firebeard.

304
00:15:08,399 --> 00:15:11,360
I used to be with the Fist of the Iron Dawn.

305
00:15:13,439 --> 00:15:14,159
What do you know?

306
00:15:14,159 --> 00:15:14,959
What's happening?

307
00:15:14,959 --> 00:15:18,079
We arrived in town a few days ago,

308
00:15:18,079 --> 00:15:23,840
and it turns out my old company was here on some unsavory business,

309
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:25,919
which is part of why I left their ranks.

310
00:15:28,159 --> 00:15:31,840
A bit of a plot has unfolded since then.

311
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:35,279
There's an elf wizard that seems to have cast a charm

312
00:15:35,279 --> 00:15:38,240
on the rest of the acts of Mirabar.

313
00:15:38,799 --> 00:15:41,600
Here in town, that has corrupted them,

314
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:44,879
and they're all in his control,

315
00:15:44,879 --> 00:15:46,639
and who knows what they're doing,

316
00:15:46,639 --> 00:15:49,039
because now we see that the city's on fire.

317
00:15:49,039 --> 00:15:51,600
Did it just start getting on fire?

318
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:54,399
I don't know.

319
00:15:54,399 --> 00:15:55,919
We were transported to...

320
00:15:56,639 --> 00:15:57,679
It's a long story.

321
00:15:57,679 --> 00:15:58,480
I don't know.

322
00:15:58,480 --> 00:16:00,480
We just got back from where we were,

323
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:02,240
and we saw the town burning.

324
00:16:02,879 --> 00:16:05,840
Okay. Well, that's not good.

325
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:09,840
We have half of our army here.

326
00:16:10,399 --> 00:16:14,000
There were 500 soldiers left in the city,

327
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:17,519
and 500 were scheduled to return before we got back.

328
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:19,519
So that's...

329
00:16:19,519 --> 00:16:20,960
If he has charmed them all,

330
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:25,920
that's a thousand soldiers that he has under his control.

331
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:28,320
Do you know anything about the charm?

332
00:16:28,960 --> 00:16:30,800
Yes. Take off all your clothes.

333
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,360
I beg your pardon?

334
00:16:33,360 --> 00:16:34,080
Who is this?

335
00:16:35,040 --> 00:16:36,240
He's asking you, Flint.

336
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:40,400
This is Thea Amastasia.

337
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:41,759
She's a druid,

338
00:16:41,759 --> 00:16:44,320
and I've been traveling with her for the last few months.

339
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:45,200
Great.

340
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:47,360
He's charmed the armor.

341
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:48,639
Charmed the armor.

342
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:49,920
Okay.

343
00:16:50,720 --> 00:16:55,200
Yes, because we met another person from the acts of Mirabar

344
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:56,080
who was named...

345
00:16:57,120 --> 00:16:57,680
Anyone?

346
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:01,520
Do you know a dwarf named Ostrich Battlehammer?

347
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:03,040
He's a close friend, yes.

348
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:03,920
We met him.

349
00:17:03,920 --> 00:17:07,200
He was uncharmed because he was off duty,

350
00:17:08,080 --> 00:17:09,440
not wearing his armor,

351
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:14,080
and he appears to be one of the only soldiers

352
00:17:14,080 --> 00:17:16,400
not affected by this charm,

353
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:20,240
and their minds appear to be gone.

354
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:21,039
I'm sorry.

355
00:17:21,039 --> 00:17:23,519
I know these are your soldiers,

356
00:17:23,519 --> 00:17:28,320
but they are overtaken by this elf,

357
00:17:28,320 --> 00:17:31,200
and he is controlling their words and their actions.

358
00:17:31,920 --> 00:17:35,039
Do you know if this is a reversible charm?

359
00:17:35,039 --> 00:17:37,039
We tried removing the armor,

360
00:17:37,039 --> 00:17:38,559
and it had no effect.

361
00:17:38,559 --> 00:17:40,640
We don't know if there's a magical cure,

362
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:42,799
but just removing the armor didn't do anything.

363
00:17:44,880 --> 00:17:49,440
So if we go in under this with our armor on,

364
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:52,480
we are at risk, as you understand,

365
00:17:52,480 --> 00:17:53,759
to become charmed as well.

366
00:17:54,319 --> 00:17:54,960
Perhaps.

367
00:17:54,960 --> 00:17:56,400
Not so crazy now, am I?

368
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:56,880
Perhaps.

369
00:17:56,880 --> 00:18:02,080
It could have been a one-time cast of a spell that he did,

370
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:04,240
but we're not exactly sure,

371
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:07,040
so it could be anything at this point.

372
00:18:07,040 --> 00:18:09,600
He may have set up some sort of mist tent

373
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:10,480
because it was hot,

374
00:18:10,480 --> 00:18:12,640
and they all walked through it wearing their armor.

375
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:15,280
Sure.

376
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:16,000
Yeah, I get it.

377
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:17,120
Anything's possible.

378
00:18:17,680 --> 00:18:18,180
Yeah.

379
00:18:20,080 --> 00:18:26,160
Okay, you don't know how you got out.

380
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:28,340
Okay.

381
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:32,640
Well, this is tough.

382
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:38,720
There is a sewer entrance into Mirabar.

383
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:43,600
I don't want to take all of my soldiers beyond this point,

384
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:46,960
really, in case whatever's happening turns them,

385
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,920
but I could come with you

386
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:54,240
and try and get in without my armor, obviously,

387
00:18:54,960 --> 00:18:57,680
and see if we can't figure things out

388
00:18:58,559 --> 00:19:01,279
and then hopefully drop whatever charm

389
00:19:01,279 --> 00:19:03,839
or figure out if we can't all come in

390
00:19:03,839 --> 00:19:05,200
to help clear the city.

391
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:08,240
We released Ostrich.

392
00:19:08,240 --> 00:19:10,319
We were all trapped in the dungeon together,

393
00:19:10,319 --> 00:19:14,319
so it's possible he escaped

394
00:19:14,319 --> 00:19:15,519
and we could find him,

395
00:19:15,519 --> 00:19:18,960
and maybe he has learned more in our absence,

396
00:19:19,840 --> 00:19:26,559
or he could now be possessed or dead,

397
00:19:28,319 --> 00:19:30,480
but you say he is a good friend of yours.

398
00:19:31,279 --> 00:19:31,440
Yes.

399
00:19:31,440 --> 00:19:32,880
If you know where he may be,

400
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:35,600
that might be a good starting destination for us.

401
00:19:35,600 --> 00:19:39,440
He's the only one we saw that wasn't under this spell.

402
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:41,039
Well, I know a couple places

403
00:19:41,039 --> 00:19:42,720
we could probably look for him.

404
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:47,039
Hopefully, the entire place hasn't been completely overrun,

405
00:19:47,039 --> 00:19:51,039
but yeah, we need to get in there somehow,

406
00:19:51,039 --> 00:19:54,879
so let's get your armor.

407
00:19:55,759 --> 00:19:58,720
Or, you know, save the town, but either one.

408
00:19:58,720 --> 00:20:00,399
We do have some armor being made.

409
00:20:03,039 --> 00:20:04,879
Okay, maybe that's a good place to go,

410
00:20:04,879 --> 00:20:07,759
because if I can't get in with my armor,

411
00:20:08,319 --> 00:20:12,720
maybe there is another armor that I can be outfit with,

412
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:14,319
but yes, let's go do that.

413
00:20:14,319 --> 00:20:16,240
He begins to take off his armor

414
00:20:16,240 --> 00:20:19,759
and give his next-in-command orders

415
00:20:19,759 --> 00:20:23,599
