00:44:21,840 --> 00:44:26,400
Well, let's go and kill some dark elf.

1082
00:44:26,400 --> 00:44:28,640
It sounds like a couple of bad options.

1083
00:44:28,640 --> 00:44:30,320
So what do you guys recommend?

1084
00:44:30,320 --> 00:44:31,440
This is your town.

1085
00:44:32,079 --> 00:44:34,000
You know the lay of the land

1086
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:35,199
way better than we do.

1087
00:44:36,719 --> 00:44:38,320
Are the tunnels the better option?

1088
00:44:39,119 --> 00:44:40,559
What do you suggest?

1089
00:44:40,559 --> 00:44:42,480
Because we have to take this guy out.

1090
00:44:42,480 --> 00:44:43,519
Osric says...

1091
00:44:43,519 --> 00:44:45,920
The tunnel, as guarded as it may be,

1092
00:44:47,360 --> 00:44:49,199
there are 500 soldiers

1093
00:44:49,199 --> 00:44:51,039
standing outside their front door.

1094
00:44:51,599 --> 00:44:53,039
I think the tunnel is going to be

1095
00:44:53,039 --> 00:44:54,480
the easiest way in.

1096
00:44:54,480 --> 00:44:56,239
That said, there will still be

1097
00:44:56,239 --> 00:44:57,679
some hard fighting to get in there,

1098
00:44:57,679 --> 00:44:58,320
though, I think.

1099
00:44:58,320 --> 00:44:59,119
Once we are in,

1100
00:44:59,119 --> 00:45:00,719
we may be able to bar the bulk

1101
00:45:00,719 --> 00:45:02,480
of their soldiers from getting in.

1102
00:45:02,480 --> 00:45:03,920
If we are able to get past

1103
00:45:03,920 --> 00:45:04,880
some of their defenses.

1104
00:45:05,679 --> 00:45:06,960
Tunnels it is.

1105
00:45:06,960 --> 00:45:08,000
Let's do it.

1106
00:45:08,000 --> 00:45:10,240
As you turn to leave,

1107
00:45:10,240 --> 00:45:12,480
Nularaaaa, you hear...

1108
00:45:12,480 --> 00:45:13,679
Well, all of you hear,

1109
00:45:13,679 --> 00:45:16,079
but the source is coming from Nularaaaa.

1110
00:45:16,079 --> 00:45:19,440
You hear a static charge,

1111
00:45:19,440 --> 00:45:22,559
like a electric shock, lightning.

1112
00:45:22,559 --> 00:45:23,519
Not that you're shocked,

1113
00:45:23,519 --> 00:45:24,880
but that kind of sound.

1114
00:45:24,880 --> 00:45:28,480
And you hear a voice crackling in.

1115
00:45:28,480 --> 00:45:31,280
The sound is coming from your arrow quiver.

1116
00:45:31,280 --> 00:45:34,160
And you hear the voice of

1117
00:45:34,160 --> 00:45:35,920
what you think is Salazar.

1118
00:45:36,880 --> 00:45:39,440
And it's coming in through static,

1119
00:45:39,440 --> 00:45:40,480
and he says...

1120
00:45:40,480 --> 00:45:42,960
Tibby, Tibby, where are you?

1121
00:45:43,840 --> 00:45:44,880
Where did you guys go?

1122
00:45:44,880 --> 00:45:47,040
We just, we just got your signal back.

1123
00:45:47,040 --> 00:45:48,880
Ah, you stupid mech.

1124
00:46:01,280 --> 00:46:04,080
Music in today's episode was by Kavin McLeod

1125
00:46:04,080 --> 00:46:06,400
of incompetech.filmmusic.io.

1126
00:46:06,400 --> 00:46:08,800
Dumbgeons & Dragons is a Dumb Dragons production.
